                        <additions>
                            <p>
                                <locus from="LCI" to="LCI" scheme="other"/>
                                <note>Top of page, in black ink by a medieval hand: four lines of text in French; bottom left corner: National Library book label with current signum.</note>
                            </p>
                        </additions>
                        <bindingDesc>
                            <binding contemporary="unknown">
                                <p>Medieval binding. Brown leather over wooden boards. 6 raised bands. <locus from="LCO" to="LCO" scheme="other"/>, top of page in black ink: <quote>N<hi rend="super">o</hi> 39. Reditus Domus Dei in vernone</quote>. <locus from="Spine" to="Spine" scheme="other"/>, on a damaged label in ink: <quote>St-s</quote>, and in print: <quote>II REDITUS DOMUS DEI DE VERNONE</quote>; stamped: <quote>A 239</quote>; National Library book label with current signum.</p>
                                <p>
                                    <dimensions type="binding">
                                        <height quantity="250" unit="mm"/>
                                        <width quantity="190" unit="mm"/>
                                        <depth quantity="50" unit="mm"/>
                                    </dimensions>
                                </p>
                                <condition>Leather worn. <locus from="Spine" to="Spine" scheme="other"/>, the leather possibly a later repair. <locus from="LCO" to="LCO" scheme="other"/> and <locus from="RCO" to="RCO" scheme="other"/>, repairs with white leather; <locus from="LCO" to="LCO" scheme="other"/>, middle of cover, outer edge: 2 holes; upper part of cover: two nails (remnats of strap); <locus from="LCO" to="LCO" scheme="other"/>: several holes and marks from a knife on the cover.</condition>
                            </binding>
                        </bindingDesc>
                    </physDesc>
                    <history>
                        <origin>
                            <p>
                                <origPlace>
                                    <placeName ref="https://www.manuscripta.se/place/100111">France</placeName>
                                    <placeName ref="https://www.manuscripta.se/place/100269">Vernon</placeName>
                                </origPlace>, <origDate notAfter="1300" notBefore="1276">13th century, last quarter</origDate>. For a discussion on the date see <bibl>
                                    <title type="short" ref="https://www.manuscripta.se/bibl/107325">Louis (1997)</title>
                                    <citedRange from="VII" to="VII" unit="page">page VII–VII.</citedRange>
                                </bibl>
                            </p>
                        </origin>
                        <provenance>
                            <p>The manuscript later belonged to <persName ref="https://www.manuscripta.se/person/102544">Paul Petau</persName>, from whom it was acquired by <persName ref="https://www.manuscripta.se/person/100086">Queen Christina</persName> and brought to Sweden. The signum on the <locus from="LCO" to="LCO" scheme="other"/> corresponds to the catalogue of 1734 (125e), where it is listed as:<quote> Phil. in 4<hi rend="super">o</hi> no 39</quote>.</p>
                        </provenance>
                        <provenance>
                            <p/>
                        </provenance>
                        <provenance>
                            <p>In <date when="1997"/> the manuscript was on loan to <placeName ref="https://www.manuscripta.se/place/100269">Vernon</placeName>.</p>
                        </provenance>
                    </history>
